      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The shadowy st. Joe river trip,\nby clean, cool Inland electric trains\nand connecting steamer Idaho, is\nof especial interest, as fine view\nof the rich meadow lands of the\nOccur d'Alene Indian reservation\nIs afforded. The round trip to\nhead of navigation is 200 miles, and\nis the most charming scenic lake\nand river trip from Spokane. Spe-\ncial Sunday rate to st. Joe, only\n$3.50; to st. Maries, 5000 Deli\ncious old fashioned country chicken\ndinner served on board the Idaho.\nTake electric trains leaving Spo-\nkane terminal sos a. m. Sunday,\nreturning $3.50 p. m. ***"
